Description: Fill out the survey according to the instructions.
Answer.q5-time-to-visit: Any time of year, but it's also fun to visit during the sculpture race which usually happens in May.
Answer.q6-why-visit: This museum features "outsider art" from artists who weren't formally trained.  The range of work is really amazing, from a sculpture of a naval ship made from hundreds of thousands of matchsticks, to a series of hand-cranked moving sculptures called automatons.  The gift shop is also surprisingly cool.

Answer.q6-why-visit: This is lovely old tavern with wooden walls that serves really awesome hand carved roast beef sandwiches.  It's tucked away in a place where most tourists don't go.
